# Code Owners — per ADR-023 §Axis 1.
# Canonical search order: .github/, root, docs/. We use .github/CODEOWNERS to keep
# the file out of the doc tree.
#
# Pattern matches glob/gitignore-style; later patterns override earlier ones.

# Global default — every change requires maintainer review until per-area owners are
# defined.
*       @Sawmonabo

# Engineering CI surface and supply-chain hygiene — security-sensitive area; tighter
# review per ADR-023 §Axis 5 (CODEOWNERS-scoped release-manifest-config.yml,
# signing-keys-pubkey-pinned.txt, .github/workflows/release-*.yml). Owner team will
# split out as @ai-sidekicks/security once GitHub team exists; until then, the
# project maintainer is the named owner.
/.github/                @Sawmonabo
/.github/workflows/      @Sawmonabo
/lefthook.yml            @Sawmonabo
/commitlint.config.mjs   @Sawmonabo
/lint-staged.config.mjs  @Sawmonabo
/renovate.json5          @Sawmonabo
/release-please-config.json       @Sawmonabo
/.release-please-manifest.json    @Sawmonabo

# Toolchain and workspace topology — load-bearing per ADR-022.
/package.json            @Sawmonabo
/pnpm-workspace.yaml     @Sawmonabo
/.npmrc                  @Sawmonabo
/.nvmrc                  @Sawmonabo
/turbo.json              @Sawmonabo
/tsconfig*.json          @Sawmonabo
/eslint.config.mjs       @Sawmonabo
/prettier.config.js      @Sawmonabo

# Governance docs — every change needs maintainer review (already covered by global
# default, restated here for clarity).
/docs/decisions/         @Sawmonabo
/docs/specs/             @Sawmonabo
/docs/plans/             @Sawmonabo
/docs/architecture/      @Sawmonabo
/CLAUDE.md               @Sawmonabo
/AGENTS.md               @Sawmonabo
/CONTRIBUTING.md         @Sawmonabo
